# Python Bot Standards

## Logging
Use `logging` instead of `print`. Every module must have its own logger:
```python
# ✅ GOOD
logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
logger.info("Task saved: %d", task_id)

# ❌ BAD
print(f"Task saved: {task_id}")
```

## Type hints
Always annotate function signatures with types. Use `Optional[T]` for nullable returns.
```python
# ✅ GOOD
def save_task(user_id: int, text: str, deadline: datetime) -> int: ...

# ❌ BAD
def save_task(user_id, text, deadline): ...
```

## Exception handling in handlers
Wrap external calls (DB, Telegram API) in try/except and log the error.
```python
# ✅ GOOD
try:
    await context.bot.send_message(...)
except Exception:
    logger.exception("Failed to send message to user %d", user_id)

# ❌ BAD
await context.bot.send_message(...)  # unhandled, will crash the handler
```

## Datetime always timezone-aware
All `datetime` objects must carry a `tzinfo` (use `ZoneInfo`). Never use naive datetimes.
```python
# ✅ GOOD
from zoneinfo import ZoneInfo
deadline = datetime(2026, 6, 12, 14, 0, tzinfo=ZoneInfo("Europe/Moscow"))

# ❌ BAD
deadline = datetime(2026, 6, 12, 14, 0)
```
